      "questionText": "Simplify $\\dfrac{a^5 \\times a^{-2}}{a^3}$.",
      "answerType": "expression",
      "correctAnswer": "$a^0 = 1$",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "$a^5 \\times a^{-2} = a^{5-2} = a^3$; then $a^3 \\div a^3$" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$a^0 = 1$ cao" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "$a^5 \\times a^{-2} = a^{5+(-2)} = a^3$",
        "$\\dfrac{a^3}{a^3} = a^{3-3} = a^0 = 1$"
      ],
      "explanation": "Use the index laws: multiply â†’ add; divide â†’ subtract indices."
    },
    {
      "id": "E1-07-Q2",
      "type": "short-answer",
      "totalMarks": 3,
      "commandWord": "calculate",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "questionText": "Calculate $\\left(\\dfrac{27}{8}\\right)^{-2/3}$.",
      "answerType": "fraction",
      "correctAnswer": "4/9",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "$\\left(\\dfrac{27}{8}\\right)^{1/3} = \\dfrac{3}{2}$" },
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "$\\left(\\dfrac{27}{8}\\right)^{2/3} = \\left(\\dfrac{3}{2}\\right)^2 = \\dfrac{9}{4}$" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$\\left(\\dfrac{27}{8}\\right)^{-2/3} = \\dfrac{4}{9}$ cao" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "$\\left(\\dfrac{27}{8}\\right)^{1/3} = \\dfrac{27^{1/3}}{8^{1/3}} = \\dfrac{3}{2}$",
        "$\\left(\\dfrac{27}{8}\\right)^{2/3} = \\left(\\dfrac{3}{2}\\right)^2 = \\dfrac{9}{4}$",
        "$\\left(\\dfrac{27}{8}\\right)^{-2/3} = \\dfrac{1}{9/4} = \\dfrac{4}{9}$"
      ],
      "explanation": "Negative index = reciprocal; fractional index $m/n$ = $n$th root, then power $m$."
    },
